## The bottom line: --

1.  Postcrossing is most popular in nordic and eastern European countries, and catching up in USA and China.

2.  Countries with higher percentage of elderly people also have higher percentage of population registered on postcrossing.

3.  Being elderly or young has no correlation with the number of postcards sent. Instead, it is wealth (GDP per capita) that correlates with the number of postcards sent on average by a member, in a country.

